items.name: Glowing_style_lycoris
items.description:
My friend saw an AI image (Midjourney) on Pinterest wielding a glowing weapon.
He wants to use "Stable Diffusion" with different models to create various styles.
It's a challenging task, and this "LORA" is not perfect.
It requires the use of various plugins to generate better images, such as ControlNet, adetailer, and i2i. You can find adetailer at https://github.com/Bing-su/adetailer.
Combining adetailer can greatly enhance the image quality, so it's highly recommended to give it a try.

If you encounter any image distortions, please try adjusting the "LoRA Block Weight" or enlarging the image. When using it, please abide by local laws, refrain from causing harm to others or engaging in illegal activities.
If you have any ideas for improving this LORA, please feel free to leave a comment.

items.name: Old Time Post Apocalyptic Enviroment
items.description:
Hello,

You can use this lora to make background scene with post apocaplytic style

Trigger word "SZ_4po enviroment"

I recommend using the wildcard here: https://civitai.com/models/70264

In case you don't want to use wildcard, play around with these prompts:

inside a post-apocalyptic library, dust-shrouded books, sagging shelves, strewn broken furniture, ceiling cobwebs.

on a post-apocalyptic kitchen, scattered rusted pots, cracked dining table, moldy open refrigerator.

inside a post-apocalyptic collapsed bedroom, dust-laden bed, peeling wallpaper, shattered mirror, moth-ravaged wardrobe.

on a post-apocalyptic living room, torn sofas, shattered tv, faded family photographs, worn carpet.

inside a post-apocalyptic nursery, broken crib, strewn dust-covered stuffed animals, peeling wallpaper.

in a post-apocalyptic abandoned workshop, scattered rusted tools, lingering oil smell, yellowed blueprints.

in a post-apocalyptic empty classroom, overturned desks, dusty chalkboard, yellowed textbooks.

inside a post-apocalyptic silent hospital ward, stained bed sheets, dusty medical equipment, lingering antiseptic odor.

on a post-apocalyptic deserted train station, rusting benches, cracked information board, graffiti-covered abandoned train.

in a post-apocalyptic crumbling cinema, torn posters, dusty projector, broken seats, lopsided screen.

on a post-apocalyptic supermarket, empty shelves, scattered trolleys, broken glass, decaying food packaging.

in a post-apocalyptic factory, rusting machinery, broken windows, discarded materials, smashed control room.

in a post-apocalyptic neglected greenhouse, shattered glass, overgrown plants, rusted tools, dried fountain.

***Update V4.0***

I improved the data set so this lora can match with many checkpoints.

Recommended settings:

Lora Weight: 0.6-0.8

Sampler: DPM++ 2M SDE Karras

Steps: 20-30

Upscale is recommended with 4x-Ultrasharp

Denoising strenght : 0.3-0.5

CFG scale: 5-7

***Update V3.0***

I updated some new concepts for the data set.

Recommended settings:

Lora Weight: 0.6-0.8

Sampler: DPM++ 2M SDE Karras

Steps: 20-30

Upscale is recommended with 4x-Ultrasharp

Denoising strenght : 0.3-0.5

CFG scale: 5-7

***UPDATE V2.0***

I made a improved version v2.0 with bigger data sets that can support better post apocalyptic overgrown style.

Recommended settings:

Lora Weight: 0.6-0.8

Sampler: DPM++ 2M SDE Karras

Steps: 20-30

Upscale is recommended with 4x-Ultrasharp

Denoising strenght : 0.3-0.5

CFG scale: 5-7

***V1.0***

Recommended settings:

Lora Weight 0.6-0.8

Sampler: DPM++ 2M SDE Karras

Steps: 30-40

Upscale to get best result

Denosing strenght 0.6

CFG 7

Welcome any feedback so I can make better version in the future!

items.name: Lohse (Divinity Original Sin 2) LoRA
items.description:
Lohse from Divinity Original Sin 2 by Larian Studios.

Works better with lower CFG vaules (3-6).

Recommended weight range is around 0.4-0.7 depending on the model and CFG vaule, I found that between 0.56-0.6 works decent enough with HiRes fix. Adetailer is highly recommended.

Weight could be reduced when using SD upscale or certain img2img actions.

**model might not render hair correctly, adding 'white stripe in hair', 'white hair stripe' 'white hair streak' or 'small white hair streak on left side' to the prompt with relative weight could help, e.g. '(redhead), (small white hair streak on left side:0.98)'; i found that this promt works decent enough.

Example promts; talojilohse standing in front of an ancient temple, (redhead), (small white hair streak on left side:0.98) / talojilohse standing in a forest / talojilohse with crop top sitting on a room.

Extra Info:

Dataset for the model was around 20 pictures including pictures from the web and in game and manually captioning images. Model quality is lower than i usally aim.

Released as an alpha, i will try to improve it further on my free time.

Crediting when using this model in merges and such is much appreciated.

If you want to support my work, buy me a Coffee!

items.name: Hugging own legs
items.description:
LoRA trained to generate a character sitting while hugging their legs. I do realize some base models already understand the concept but don't tend get it right. This should help. There may still be small issues with mixed up limbs, but I can't fix all SD issues with a lora :)

Please rate and leave a like if you enjoyed it! And be sure to follow to check out the upcoming models.

Trigger: hugging own legs

You can adjust the lora weight depending on how well the base model is familiar with the concept.

Additional info

I make these models for fun and for the challenge and release them for free for everyone to enjoy, for non-commercial use (see license). The one thing I ask of you is to provide rating and feedback! That helps me understand where I can improve and helps me stay motivated to produce more content! I accept suggestions or requests here or on Civitai discord server.

You can also check my more polished images and upcoming models on my pixiv profile.

items.name: FurryVerse
items.description:
FurryVerse - v1

This model is the result of several different models I merged with the intent to achieve a versatile all-in-one style checkpoint for furry, feral and anime styles.

It took me several days to create this and used many different techniques like cosine, block weight merging and utilizing training on top.

To achieve different styles and results, you have to adjust the sampling method, cfg scale and clip skip. This is because of the wide range this model is capable of and so you have to be good at prompt crafting.

Please note: The core of this model consists of furry checkpoints, hence it mainly creates anthropomorphic characters, you can also have a wide range of humans or human like characters with the according prompt.

Useful Extensions

  • !After Detailer (automatic inpainting for faces and hands to improve bad faces and hands)

  • ControlNet (let's you control image composition, pose and almost anything you could desire)

  • Agent Scheduler (essentially a queuing system to increase your workflow)

  • Ultimate SD Upscale (good for users with limited VRAM as you can upscale to increase quality)

  • e621 Prompt (You can copy and paste any e621 post URL to get a prompt to generate an image as shown in the showcase)

Useful LoRAs

  • Detail Tweaker LoRA

  • Add More Details - Detail Enhancer / Tweaker

Useful prompt embeddings

  • EasyNegative

  • Fast Negative Embedding

  • BadDream + UnrealisticDream

  • veryBadImageNegative

  • bad_prompt

  • Deep Negative

items.name: SpiritMix - Soft and Cutesy (2.5D Anime)
items.description:
Update : I've uploaded a new pruned model at fp16 with a baked in VAE as people had suggested. It produces the exact same images as before but now doesn't require manually applying a VAE!

Welcome to the world of SpiritMix and my first openly public blend! This model was an experiment to try and get a more "3D" looking anime model while retaining a bright and soft look. The goal was to keep those anime proportions and faces, along with those expressive faces, while still offering detailed environments and outfits. Honestly it turned out much better than expected, but struggles in a couple areas I'll cover later. Please share your results, I want to know what this thing can do! (and I want to see your creative gens!)

< ----- ----- ----- >

Discord - The Broken Chatbox - https://discord.gg/h3vB7S4FEw

Donations! =^-^= - https://ko-fi.com/michaelpstanich

< ----- ----- ----- >

Model Name :
SpiritMix - Soft and Cutesy (2.5D Anime).safetensor

Experimental Name :
_SpiritMerge1_1-7-4-2_.safetensors

Focus :
Soft 2.5D Anime Style with a soft 3D look

SFW / NSFW :
Does SFW and soft NSFW. Some SFW prompts can still show NSFW so I wouldn't consider this a 'safe for public use' model.

Bias :
Heavy female human bias
Tends to make faces look younger (subjectively looks young adult-teen looking in most cases)
Likes to generate Lewd leaning images with certain prompts, even SFW prompts (silly SD, being horny >.>)

< ----- ----- ----- >

So what is SpiritMix - Soft and Cutesy (2.5D Anime)?
This Checkpoint Merge is a blend of various SD1.5 models which tries to create a soft and bright presentation without giving up too much detail and keeping that "3D" look of 2.5D anime. I consider this mix to be experimental but it's turned out quite usable so why not share? This specific merge was part of a merge tree of over 40-ish merges so the specific recipe is kinda lost, but contains various anime models, specifically starting with 'simple 2D' and 'flat and bright' models then merging with '3D / Realistic' leaning models. The mix pool contains both Public and Private models, all of which are mixes themselves.

< ----- ----- ----- >

Suggested Settings :
Add "best quality" and "highly detailed" to positive prompt, avoid using "realistic" and "masterpiece" in your negative or positive prompt.
Avoid ancestral samplers like Eular A, the random noise seems to cause issues and images don't resolve well.
High-ish step count (I typically used 34 with DPM++ SDE Karras), helps to resolve small artifacts and issues.
Image size of 512x512, 768x768, or 512x768, really struggles on wider images, deforming human arms/legs more frequently
HiRes Fix, simple upscalers work well but requires high steps, latent tends to try adding non-existing detail and breaks figures (I mainly Used R-ESRGAN 4x+ at 0.36)
Clip-Skip 2, tends to produce better results but isn't required
VAE with soft color grading

< ----- ----- ----- >

What this mix does well :
Soft and Cutesy Female Characters
Young Adult / Teen-like Characters
Cute Anime Faces
Bright environments with simple structures
Clothes, apparently
Breasts X.x

< ----- ----- ----- >

What this mix struggles with :
Hands can be a major struggle, higher resolutions and ControlNet helps
Some body shapes don't form well and some body prompts are often ignored (For example, if you include Large Thighs and Flat Chest, it will prioritize Large and include Large Breasts instead, no matter the weights. The data sets most likely didn't include some body types so the tokens don't exist for them)
Doesn't usually do well with Hardcore NSFW stuff, can do it but often messes up anatomy of certain body parts with missing details.

< ----- ----- ----- >

Other quirks / issues :
Sometimes characters are cross-eyed when the head is lower res, kinda silly looking.

items.name: Asura (DirtyEro) LoRA
items.description:
Asura from the artist DirtyEro. Works well on 0.6-1.0. Training done on NAI.

Trigger: "asuraEro, colored skin" always needed, "slit pupils, toned, muscular, abs, navel" for accuracy.

Outfits/Suggestions:

  • Classic: "backwards hat, spikes, choker, collar, necklace, hoop earrings, black gloves, fingerless gloves, crop top, fishnets, ((fishnet top)), belt, denim jeans, torn jeans" Beware "Fingerless gloves" are still evil and will give a hard time with fingers.

  • Lower the weight to get better results with other choices of clothing but it is very flexible even at higher weights.

  • Optional: She has a tail but it is RNG so try with "Demon tail, tail" if you want.

Sometimes her skin/hair will become paler/brighter so Prompt "Red skin" or "Dark hair" to help bring it back.

Red demon girl with abs is an easy sell for me and so here we are. Data was limited but of a high quality so the end result is very accurate to the original. I hope you all enjoy.

Feedback and reviews are always appreciated.

The Hangover is a 2009 American comedy film. It is the first installment in The Hangover trilogy. The film stars Bradley Cooper, Ed Helms, Zach Galifianakis, Heather Graham, Justin Bartha, Ken Jeong, and Jeffrey Tambor. It tells the story of Phil Wenneck (Cooper), Stu Price (Helms), Alan Garner (Galifianakis), and Doug Billings (Bartha), who travel to Las Vegas for a bachelor party to celebrate Doug's impending marriage. However, Phil, Stu, and Alan wake up with Doug missing and no memory of the previous night's events, and must find the groom before the wedding can take place.

Terrence Stephen McQueen (March 24, 1930Â â€“ November 7, 1980)[4] was an American actor. His antihero persona, emphasized during the height of the counterculture of the 1960s, made him a top box-office draw for his films of the 1960s and 1970s. He was nicknamed the "King of Cool" and used the alias Harvey Mushman in motor races.

McQueen received an Academy Award nomination for his role in The Sand Pebbles (1966). His other popular films include The Cincinnati Kid (1965), Nevada Smith (1966), The Thomas Crown Affair (1968), Bullitt (1968), The Getaway (1972), and Papillon (1973). In addition, he starred in the all-star ensemble films The Magnificent Seven (1960), The Great Escape (1963), and The Towering Inferno (1974).

In 1974, McQueen became the highest-paid movie star in the world, although he did not act in film for another four years. He was combative with directors and producers, but his popularity placed him in high demand and enabled him to command the largest salaries.[5]
